# Built binary (root .gitignore backstops this via zdoc-*-renderer / *.exe)
zdoc-html-renderer
zdoc-html-renderer.exe
render_test
*.o

# Local test render output
out/
out2/
example-output/

# Test sources + fixtures - matches the same convention already used in
# extractor/doc_extractor and renderer/md_renderer (tests stay local, not
# tracked).
tests/

# Superseded now that html_render() reads the daemon's module_tree tables
# and parsed Module array directly (no JSON, no subprocess, no
# doc_extractor stage) - kept on disk, not tracked, in case revisited:
#  - json.c/h: the JSON reader, no longer needed at all.
#  - html_model.c/h: the JSON-parsing model layer, superseded first by
#    doc_extractor's DxModel and now removed entirely along with it.
#  - main.c: the old CLI driver (./zdoc-html-renderer file.json).
#    html_renderer is a library now - see tests/render_test.c for how it's
#    exercised.
#  - sample.json, data/*.json, run_tests.sh: the old JSON fixtures and their
#    test runner; tests/render_test.c builds the same kind of content as C
#    structures instead.
_disabled/
